jbt.execution.core
Class BTLibraryFactory

java.lang.Object
  jbt.execution.core.BTLibraryFactory

public class BTLibraryFactory
extends java.lang.Object

The BTLibraryFactory implements the simple factory pattern, and allows clients of the framework to create instances of IBTLibrary composed of behaviour trees.

createBTLibrary

public static IBTLibrary createBTLibrary(java.util.List<IBTLibrary> libraries)
Creates a BT library that contains all the BTs contained in the libraries of libraries. If several trees are referenced by the same name, only the last one (according to its order in the input libraries) will remain.

Parameters:
libraries - the list with all the libraries whose BTs will contain the returned BT library.
Returns:
a BT library that contains all the BTs contained in the libraries of libraries.

createBTLibrary

public static IBTLibrary createBTLibrary(java.util.List<ModelTask> behaviourTrees,
                                         java.util.List<java.lang.String> names)
Creates a BT library that contains all the behaviour trees in behaviourTrees. The name of the trees are specified in names, so, for instance, the i-th element in names represents the name of the i-th tree in behaviourTrees. If several trees are referenced by the same name, only the last one (according to its order in the input lists) will remain.

Parameters:
behaviourTrees - the list with the trees that the BT library will contain.
names - the list with the names of the trees.
Returns:
a BT library that contains all the behaviour trees in the list behaviourTrees.
